# LaTeX Compilation & Clean Code Rules

Rules and guardrails for editing and compiling LaTeX files in this repository.

## 1. Directory & File Modularity
- **Never add package imports directly in section files.** All packages must go inside [preamble/packages.tex](preamble/packages.tex).
- **Never define macros in section files.** All macros must go inside [preamble/macros.tex](preamble/macros.tex).
- Keep slides modular under `sections/`. Never dump massive content straight into `main.tex`.

## 2. Compilation Safety & Escapes
- **Special Characters:** Always escape special LaTeX characters in regular text:
  - `%` -> `\%`
  - `_` -> `\_`
  - `&` -> `\&`
  - `$` -> `\$`
  - `#` -> `\#`
- **Braces and Scopes:** Ensure every `\begin{env}` has a corresponding `\end{env}`.
- **Paths:** Use relative paths relative to `main.tex`. For instance, `\input{sections/01_intro}` rather than absolute or deep paths.

## 3. Package and Command Best Practices
- Use modern package alternatives:
  - Prefer `booktabs` for tables (use `\toprule`, `\midrule`, `\bottomrule`). Avoid vertical lines (`|`) in tables as they reduce academic professionalism.
  - Use `\texttt{}` for inline code or command words.
  - Use `\lstlisting` or `\begin{semiverbatim}` only in `[fragile]` frames.
